parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping and Loss of Motive Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and loss of motive power can cause the vehicle to stall or lose acceleration, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips
the vehicle loses motive power
the vehicle shifts into neutral without warning
the check engine warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle jerks and shifts roughly
the vehicle fails to immediately accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, making it difficult to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive axle can cause a loss of power, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The drive axle fails
the bolts holding the axle to the transmission shear
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to refuse to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks. Additionally, it can affect the operation of various systems, including the AWD system, brakes, and tire sensors, which can compromise vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: The vehicle refuses to start
electrical problems
computer problems
errors with drive mode unavailable
tire sensor damage or low warnings
and brakes squeaking when in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless entry system can cause inconvenience and potential safety risks, as the driver may be unable to unlock the doors or access the vehicle.
symptoms: The doors fail to unlock while using the key fob
inability to access the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake noise and vibration can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, which can affect vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: Brakes squeak when in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbag Deployment in Crash Situations
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in crash situations can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality to occupants, particularly in high-impact collisions.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in crash situations
despite meeting the deployment threshold
leaving occupants vulnerable to injury or fatality.
